sql:
SELECT AVG(income_id) AS average_income_id
FROM respondent_demographics
WHERE demographic_group = 'Middle income';

SELECT r.name
FROM respondents r
WHERE r.respondent_id IN (
    SELECT respondent_id FROM responses WHERE question_id = 1
) AND r.demographic_group = (
    SELECT demographic_group FROM respondent_demographics WHERE respondent_id = 1
);

SELECT question_id, COUNT(DISTINCT response) 
FROM answers 
GROUP BY question_id;

external_knowledge:
- "garden" metaphorically refers to the topic of questions;
- "blooms" and "bouquet of responses" metaphorically represent the responses to those questions;
- The question seeks the topic with the highest number of responses.
